Program: Free Thinking
Title: Sleep, Sleeplessness and Creativity
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04wmx7k
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 7 Jan 2015
We spend nearly a third of our life doing it and we still don't really know why so Rana Mitter explores why we sleep with pioneering researcher into the body clock, Russell Foster; Matt Berry, actor, comedian and writer who wrestles with insomnia; Brigitte Steger who has explored Japanese and other global sleeping cultures and Katharine Craik, a renaissance scholar whose new opera project for children is called Watching...back in the 16th century the watching hours were part of a segmented sleep pattern which only disappeared with the industrial revolution. Producer: Jacqueline Smith. Show less